Police Officers in the Arusha region have been urged to refrain from getting involved in politics and instead concentrate on protecting citizens and their properties. Assistant Commissioner of Police (ACP) Simon Pasua said this on Monday during a ceremony that aimed to congratulate police officers who performed well in the year 2022 in the Region. The ACP stated that the main responsibility of police officers is to solve their various complaints from citizens adding that they can only be fans of other social issues including football and not political parties. Meanwhile, he congratulated those officers who did well last year while encouraging them to maintain the good performance so as to bring effectiveness in the force as well as being promoted.